{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":140,"text":"Some years ago,"},{"time":1731,"text":"I stumbled across a simple design exercise"},{"time":5175,"text":"that helps people understand\nand solve complex problems,"},{"time":8780,"text":"and like many of these design exercises,\nit kind of seems trivial at first,"},{"time":12867,"text":"but under deep inspection,"},{"time":14611,"text":"it turns out that it reveals\nunexpected truths"},{"time":17331,"text":"about the way that we collaborate\nand make sense of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20662,"text":"The exercise has three parts"},{"time":22264,"text":"and begins with something\nthat we all know how to do,"},{"time":24749,"text":"which is how to make toast."},{"time":27489,"text":"It begins with a clean sheet of paper,\na felt marker,"},{"time":30809,"text":"and without using any words,\nyou begin to draw how to make toast."},{"time":34940,"text":"And most people draw something like this."},{"time":37118,"text":"They draw a loaf of bread, \nwhich is sliced, then put into a toaster."},{"time":40498,"text":"The toast is then deposited for some time."},{"time":42744,"text":"It pops up, and then voila!\nAfter two minutes, toast and happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49045,"text":"Now, over the years, I've collected\nmany hundreds of drawings of these toasts,"},{"time":53643,"text":"and some of them are very good,"},{"time":55403,"text":"because they really illustrate\nthe toast-making process quite clearly."},{"time":58869,"text":"And then there are some that are,\nwell, not so good."},{"time":62166,"text":"They really suck, actually, because\nyou don't know what they're trying to say."},{"time":67344,"text":"Under close inspection,"},{"time":69271,"text":"some reveal some aspects of toast-making\nwhile hiding others."},{"time":72754,"text":"So there's some\nthat are all about the toast,"},{"time":75424,"text":"and all about the transformation of toast."},{"time":78164,"text":"And there's others\nthat are all about the toaster,"},{"time":80764,"text":"and the engineers love to draw\nthe mechanics of this."},{"time":84094,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":85504,"text":"And then there are others\nthat are about people."},{"time":87875,"text":"It's about visualizing\nthe experience that people have."},{"time":91723,"text":"And then there are others that are about\nthe supply chain of making toast"},{"time":95236,"text":"that goes all the way back to the store."},{"time":97226,"text":"It goes through the supply chain\nnetworks of teleportation"},{"time":100663,"text":"and all the way back\nto the field and wheat,"},{"time":103890,"text":"and one all actually goes\nall the way back to the Big Bang."},{"time":106700,"text":"So it's crazy stuff."},{"time":108904,"text":"But I think it's obvious"},{"time":110757,"text":"that even though these drawings\nare really wildly different,"},{"time":114263,"text":"they share a common quality,\nand I'm wondering if you can see it."},{"time":117366,"text":"Do you see it? What's common about these?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":119743,"text":"Most drawings have nodes and links."},{"time":123118,"text":"So nodes represent the tangible objects\nlike the toaster and people,"},{"time":128468,"text":"and links represent\nthe connections between the nodes."},{"time":131974,"text":"And it's the combination\nof links and nodes"},{"time":134807,"text":"that produces a full systems model,"},{"time":136920,"text":"and it makes our private\nmental models visible"},{"time":139845,"text":"about how we think something works."},{"time":142878,"text":"So that's the value of these things."},{"time":144709,"text":"What's interesting about\nthese systems models"},{"time":146817,"text":"is how they reveal\nour various points of view."},{"time":149002,"text":"So for example, Americans\nmake toast with a toaster."},{"time":152623,"text":"That seems obvious."},{"time":154144,"text":"Whereas many Europeans\nmake toast with a frying pan, of course,"},{"time":158114,"text":"and many students make toast with a fire."},{"time":162391,"text":"I don't really understand this.\nA lot of MBA students do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165610,"text":"So you can measure the complexity\nby counting the number of nodes,"},{"time":169375,"text":"and the average illustration\nhas between four and eight nodes."},{"time":173297,"text":"Less than that, the drawing seems trivial,"},{"time":176292,"text":"but it's quick to understand,"},{"time":178545,"text":"and more than 13, the drawing\nproduces a feeling of map shock."},{"time":183618,"text":"It's too complex."},{"time":185121,"text":"So the sweet spot is between 5 and 13."},{"time":187664,"text":"So if you want to communicate\nsomething visually,"},{"time":190294,"text":"have between five and 13 nodes\nin your diagram."},{"time":194021,"text":"So though we may not\nbe skilled at drawing,"},{"time":196725,"text":"the point is that we intuitively know\nhow to break down complex things"},{"time":200856,"text":"into simple things and then \nbring them back together again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204116,"text":"So this brings us to our second part of \nthe exercise,"},{"time":207337,"text":"which is how to make toast,"},{"time":208913,"text":"but now with sticky notes\nor with cards."},{"time":211713,"text":"So what happens then?"},{"time":214041,"text":"Well, with cards, most people\ntend to draw clear, more detailed,"},{"time":217462,"text":"and more logical nodes."},{"time":219740,"text":"You can see the step by step\nanalysis that takes place,"},{"time":223317,"text":"and as they build up their model,\nthey move their nodes around,"},{"time":226549,"text":"rearranging them like Lego blocks."},{"time":229129,"text":"Now, though this might seem trivial,\nit's actually really important."},{"time":233184,"text":"This rapid iteration of expressing\nand then reflecting and analyzing"},{"time":237912,"text":"is really the only way\nin which we get clarity."},{"time":241263,"text":"It's the essence of the design process."},{"time":243911,"text":"And systems theorists do tell us"},{"time":245620,"text":"that the ease with which\nwe can change a representation"},{"time":249182,"text":"correlates to our willingness\nto improve the model."},{"time":253447,"text":"So sticky note systems\nare not only more fluid,"},{"time":257239,"text":"they generally produce\nway more nodes than static drawings."},{"time":261279,"text":"The drawings are much richer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263010,"text":"And this brings us\nto our third part of the exercise,"},{"time":265575,"text":"which is to draw how to make toast,\nbut this time in a group."},{"time":269509,"text":"So what happens then?"},{"time":271271,"text":"Well, here's what happens."},{"time":272883,"text":"It starts out messy,\nand then it gets really messy,"},{"time":276500,"text":"and then it gets messier,"},{"time":278125,"text":"but as people refine the models,"},{"time":280052,"text":"the best nodes become more prominent,"},{"time":282583,"text":"and with each iteration,\nthe model becomes clearer"},{"time":285160,"text":"because people build\non top of each other's ideas."},{"time":288434,"text":"What emerges is a unified systems model"},{"time":291917,"text":"that integrates the diversity\nof everyone's individual points of view,"},{"time":296057,"text":"so that's a really different outcome"},{"time":297977,"text":"from what usually happens \nin meetings, isn't it?"},{"time":300648,"text":"So these drawings can contain\n20 or more nodes,"},{"time":303620,"text":"but participants don't feel map shock"},{"time":305849,"text":"because they participate in the building\nof their models themselves."},{"time":310074,"text":"Now, what's also really interesting,\nthat the groups spontaneously mix"},{"time":313395,"text":"and add additional layers\nof organization to it."},{"time":316854,"text":"To deal with contradictions, for example,"},{"time":318864,"text":"they add branching patterns\nand parallel patterns."},{"time":321684,"text":"Oh, and by the way,\nif they do it in complete silence,"},{"time":324907,"text":"they do it much better\nand much more quickly."},{"time":327663,"text":"Really interesting --\ntalking gets in the way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330205,"text":"So here's some key lessons\nthat can emerge from this."},{"time":333897,"text":"First, drawing helps us\nunderstand the situations"},{"time":336476,"text":"as systems with nodes\nand their relationships."},{"time":339748,"text":"Movable cards produce\nbetter systems models,"},{"time":343388,"text":"because we iterate much more fluidly."},{"time":346118,"text":"And then the group notes produce \nthe most comprehensive models"},{"time":349332,"text":"because we synthesize\nseveral points of view."},{"time":352689,"text":"So that's interesting."},{"time":354275,"text":"When people work together\nunder the right circumstances,"},{"time":357581,"text":"group models are much better\nthan individual models."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360692,"text":"So this approach works really great\nfor drawing how to make toast,"},{"time":365639,"text":"but what if you wanted to draw\nsomething more relevant or pressing,"},{"time":369528,"text":"like your organizational vision,\nor customer experience,"},{"time":374636,"text":"or long-term sustainability?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":376940,"text":"There's a visual revolution\nthat's taking place"},{"time":380446,"text":"as more organizations\nare addressing their wicked problems"},{"time":383859,"text":"by collaboratively drawing them out."},{"time":386645,"text":"And I'm convinced that those who see\ntheir world as movable nodes and links"},{"time":391267,"text":"really have an edge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393391,"text":"And the practice is really pretty simple."},{"time":395469,"text":"You start with a question,\nyou collect the nodes,"},{"time":398371,"text":"you refine the nodes,\nyou do it over again,"},{"time":401459,"text":"you refine and refine and refine,\nand the patterns emerge,"},{"time":406768,"text":"and the group gets clarity\nand you answer the question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413070,"text":"So this simple act of visualizing\nand doing over and over again"},{"time":419112,"text":"produces some really remarkable outcomes."},{"time":421694,"text":"What's really important to know"},{"time":423581,"text":"is that it's the conversations\nthat are the important aspects,"},{"time":427271,"text":"not just the models themselves."},{"time":429596,"text":"And these visual frames of reference"},{"time":431384,"text":"can grow to several hundreds\nor even thousands of nodes."},{"time":435982,"text":"So, one example is from\nan organization called Rodale."},{"time":439000,"text":"Big publishing company."},{"time":440486,"text":"They lost a bunch of money one year,"},{"time":442622,"text":"and their executive team for three days\nvisualized their entire practice."},{"time":446964,"text":"And what's interesting is that\nafter visualizing the entire business,"},{"time":452886,"text":"systems upon systems,"},{"time":454650,"text":"they reclaimed \n50 million dollars of revenue,"},{"time":457716,"text":"and they also moved from a D rating \nto an A rating from their customers."},{"time":462734,"text":"Why? Because there's\nalignment from the executive team."},{"time":466329,"text":"So I'm now on a mission\nto help organizations"},{"time":469742,"text":"solve their wicked problems\nby using collaborative visualization,"},{"time":474456,"text":"and on a site that I've produced\ncalled drawtoast.com,"},{"time":477474,"text":"I've collected a bunch of best practices."},{"time":480678,"text":"and so you can learn\nhow to run a workshop here,"},{"time":483441,"text":"you can learn more about\nthe visual language"},{"time":485584,"text":"and the structure of links and nodes that\nyou can apply to general problem-solving,"},{"time":490500,"text":"and download examples of various templates"},{"time":493705,"text":"for unpacking the thorny problems\nthat we all face in our organizations."},{"time":498998,"text":"So the seemingly trivial\ndesign exercise of drawing toast"},{"time":502620,"text":"helps us get clear, engaged and aligned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506661,"text":"So next time you're confronted\nwith an interesting challenge,"},{"time":509609,"text":"remember what design has to teach us."},{"time":511943,"text":"Make your ideas visible,\ntangible, and consequential."},{"time":515774,"text":"It's simple, it's fun, it's powerful,"},{"time":518932,"text":"and I believe it's an idea\nworth celebrating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522082,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523902,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}